<headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 28 at 3:31AM EST  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...INCREASED FIRE DANGER FOR THE NORTH CAROLINA FOOTHILLS AND
PIEDMONT TODAY...
The combination of strong west winds and low humidities today,
along with drying fuels, will lead to an increase in erratic fire
behavior in the foothills and piedmont of North Carolina,
especially in the afternoon.
Burning is highly discouraged. Please refer to your local burn
permitting authorities on whether you can burn. If you do burn,
use extreme caution, since fires can quickly get out of hand
under these conditions.</description>
